I guess, you&#x27;re right - for naive implementation it should fall with error, not a segfault. Maybe I just add a check for realloc result.<p>As for qsort implementation - I was confused by glibc sources ;-) What I&#x27;ve found was a slow but in-place implementation, and what you&#x27;ve shown me is an actual implementation that invokes an in-place variant when allocation was failed:<p><pre><code>  tmp = malloc (size);
  __set_errno (save);
  if (tmp == NULL)
    {
      /* Couldn&#x27;t get space, so use the slower algorithm
         that doesn&#x27;t need a temporary array.  */
      _quicksort (b, n, s, cmp, arg);
      return;
    }
</code></pre>
Thanks for feedback!
